  "metadata": {
    "title": "Crops by NPK Effect on Soil",
    "description": "Categorization of Indian crops based on whether they deplete or replenish Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), and Potassium (K) in the soil. Useful for nutrient-based crop rotation planning.",
    "note": "Legumes generally fix Nitrogen. Most cereals and vegetables are N-depleting. Few crops affect P or K significantly unless intercropped or fertilized accordingly."
